The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Jewellery store fraud
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Jewellery store fraud
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Customers of a jewellery store in Salt Lakes AE block lodged police complaints on Friday alleging that they were duped of Rs 2 lakh by the owner. According to the complainants, the owner did not deliver their jewellery on time despite taking an advance from them. Police said customers found the store locked on Friday. The owner is absconding.        
	Energy plea: The high court on Friday directed the central and state governments to file affidavits stating their plans to switch from conventional energy like thermal power to non-conventional forms like solar power. The division bench of Chief Justice M.S. Shah and Justice B. Bhattacharya also directed several central and state power utilities to file reports stating the merits and demerits of putting non-conventional energy to everyday use. The order was passed on the basis of a petition by environment activist Subhash Dutta.        
	Film-maker dead: Raj Basu, the US-based director of Bengali film Piyalir Password which is yet to be released, died of multi-organ failure on Thursday at a hospital in Virginia. He was 52. Piyalir Password stars Rituparna Sengupta, Roopa Ganguly, Sabyasachi Chakraborty and Koushik Sen.        
	Security drill: Naval commandos conducted security drills at Taj Bengal, Park Street Metro station, Elgin Road, Sealdah station and the Gariahat crossing between 7am and 4pm on Friday. The drills were meant to check the preparedness of Calcutta polices Quick Reaction Team.        
	Power supply: Power supply may be affected in Kumarpara, Gausala, Benaras Road, Liluah and adjoining areas between 10am and 3pm on Saturday because of maintenance work.        
	Braveheart treatment: Tapasi Chanda Das, the 18-year-old who was shot by goons at a petrol pump in Patuli, underwent an MRI scan on Friday at the private hospital where she is admitted. Her right hand is paralysed.        
	Life sentence: Satya Das, 32, and Udayan Barua, 30, were sentenced to life imprisonment by the Howrah additional district judge on Friday for murdering Prabir Khan, Asis Guchait and Sambhu Das over a dispute and dumping their bodies on the tracks between Konnagar and Rishra stations in July 2000.         
	Boy injured: Sanjay Mondal, 4, was injured after a car dashed him near Udayna Park in Behala on Friday afternoon. Police said the mishap occurred when the boy was crossing the road. He was taken to Vidyasagar Hospital with head injuries. The driver was detained.        
	Body found: The decomposed body of a mentally challenged woman in her late-30s was found inside her first-floor flat on Mahendra Banerjee Road in Behala on Friday. Police suspect that Jaya Talukdar had died a few days back but her mother Gita, 70, who is also mentally unstable was unaware of it.         
	Cannon dug up: Civic officials working on a drainage project in Jyoti Nagar Colony in the North Port police station area dug up a 10ft long cannon on Friday afternoon.                                                                                                                                                          
